citations:
    citation-affc-sansa-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Sansa I"
            text_from_source: "A Lannister always pays his debts, thought Alayne Stone. But so do the Lannisters' enemies."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Sansa Stark (writing as Alayne Stone). Set in the Eyrie. Sansa is helping plan the tourney of the Gates in the Vale with Petyr Baelish (Littlefinger), who has posed as her father. She interacts with Lord Robert Arryn (Robin, the sickly Lord of the Eyrie) and helps manage his fragile moods. The Lords Declarant of the Vale arrive (Nestor Royce, Symond Templeton, Benedar Belmore, Horton Redfort, Lyn Corbray, and others) demanding Littlefinger step down as Lord Protector. Littlefinger outmaneuvers them by hosting a feast. Ser Lyn Corbray makes a threatening scene that appears orchestrated by Littlefinger. Myranda Royce (daughter of Nestor Royce) becomes Sansa's companion. Harrold Hardyng ('Harry the Heir') is identified as Robert Arryn's heir, and Littlefinger plans for Sansa to marry him. Key figures: Petyr Baelish, Lord Robert Arryn, Maester Colemon, Mord (gaoler), Oswell (Littlefinger's steward), Myranda Royce, Lord Nestor Royce, the Lords Declarant, Harry the Heir (Ser Harrold Hardyng), Ser Lyn Corbray."
